===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{lb|en|economics|politics}} Practicing or representing governmental [[noninterference]], or minimal interference, ''especially'' in economic affairs; pertaining to [[free market|free-market]] [[capitalism]].
#: ''I think the city should take a '''laissez faire''' approach to this; getting involved would only make things worse.''
# {{lb|en|economics|politics}} Advocating such noninterference.
#: ''The Senator claims to be '''laissez faire''', but he voted in favor of the subsidies.''
# {{lb|en|economics}} Resulting from such noninterference.
#: ''The price ceiling was well below the '''laissez faire''' price that demand would have supported, so there were always shortages.''
# {{lb|en|of a person}} Avoiding interference in other people's affairs; choosing to [[live and let live]].

